<br>
1. Light Roleplay Guild (army atmosphere)<br>
<br>
First off, we are sort of a roleplay guild, but not the type your used to. We don't roleplay good vs evil, as many guilds do. We loosely roleplay that our guild is a military army. Members all have a rank, and that can be raised by attending raids and helping out other guild members. There is absolutely no restrictions based on class or race.<br>
<br>
<br>
2. We are a friends guild, not a UBER guild<br>
<br>
We are NOT a uber guild, nor do we aspire to be. Yes we have several level 50+ members, but the goal of the guild is to have fun and enjoy the time spent online, not to spend every day raiding. So if your joining with the thought that the guild will be competiting with Fire and Fury or Resolution, don't, because we wont be.<br>
<br>
We will raid, likely 1 to 2 times a week. Either friday/saturdays, or one weekend day + one week day. We will try to make the most of the raid times, and leave the rest of the week open for people to just do whatever they want.<br>
<br>
<br>
3. We have divisions set up in the guild<br>
<br>
Upon joining the guild, you will be placed in a division. Currently there are 2 divisions in the guild:<br>
<br>
Alpha Division (levels 46-65): Pablo is the commanding officer in this division<br>
Bravo Division (levels 10-45): Luciferus is the commanding officer in this division<br>
<br>
If your interested in joining, you should speak with the CO of the appropriate division. (either Pablo or Luciferus)<br>
<br>
Also, the commanding officers are responsible for organizing and running events for their respective division. And any members that have requests for raids, or need guild help with something, should contact their commanding officer.<br>
<br>
ALPHA DIVISION GO GO GO!<br>
<br>
<br>
4. Your rank upon entering the Soldiers of Warfare<br>
<br>
When you first join the guild, your given the rank of Private. Once the 2 week probation is up, your promoted to Corporal. Each rank provides different privileges in the guild. You can view our message board for a full explanation of each rank and what it entails.<br>
<br>
<br>
5. How are we recruiting?<br>
<br>
Basically anyone that enjoys everquest, that would like to join an easy going guild, is welcome to join. The only limit being is that you must be atleast level 10+. We dont want to be seeing a bunch of newbie questions in guild chat, like &quot;how do I attack?&quot; heh.<br>
<br>
And if your interested in joining, make sure being in the guild is something you want to do. I dont want people that will join and leave 2 days later. I want people that will be around to develop friendships and relationships with the other members. <br>
<br>
<br>
6. What is the current size of our guild?<br>
<br>
Our guild was just created 2 days ago, so were quite small yet. We have 10 players that are level 51+, and we have 6 players that are in the 25 to 45 range. (I need to update the roster)<br>
<br>
Expect this number to grow a little over the next few days.<br>
<br>
<br>
7. What types of raids can we expect from the guild?<br>
<br>
Well, it really depends on which division your in. Luciferus has a few plans for raids in some dungeons for the 35 to 45 crowd.<br>
<br>
As for Pablo, he has some plans for some umbral plains raids, kael raids, PoG raids, and some ssra raids once we have a few more members.<br>
<br>
<br>
8. Who runs the guild? And they ever done this before?<br>
<br>
I run the guild with my character Pablo. (I play a couple characters).<br>
I have run 2 other guilds in the past, both on another server. The first guild was a learning experience for me, the 2nd one was a smaller guild of about 30 members, but was quite successful.<br>
<br>
Since then, I got involved in a lot of raiding, in the past 2 guilds I was in. First I was in Blades of Wrath on torvonnilous, Then in Fire and Fury on firiona vie for a few months. I'm no expert or anything at raiding, but I do have some raid experience and I think this will be a big benefit to the guild. <br>
